{
  "texts": [
    "One patient (0.8%) developed a Grade 1 CRS event after the fourth or later dose of elranatamab (Figure 4).",
    "Eighteen (15.1%) patients had more than one CRS event.",
    "Tocilizumab and corticosteroids were used in 22.7% and 8.4% of patients with CRS, respectively.",
    "ICANS occurred in 4 of 119 patients (3.4%), and all events were grade 1 or 2.",
    "Supportive treatment for ICANS included corticosteroids (1.7%), tocilizumab (1.7%), and levetiracetam for seizure prevention (0.8%)."
  ]
}